<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Software Engineering on Shdennlin's Blog</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/categories/software-engineering/</link><description>Recent content in Software Engineering on Shdennlin's Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 09 May 2022 00:00:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.shdennlin.com/categories/software-engineering/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Prevent SSH from disconnecting from timing out</title><link>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/prevent-ssh-from-disconnecting-from-timing-out/</link><pubDate>Mon, 09 May 2022 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.shdennlin.com/p/prevent-ssh-from-disconnecting-from-timing-out/</guid><description>&lt;p>When you use ssh to connect the remote server, but there is no operation for a long time, it&amp;rsquo;s annoying issue that disconnects from timing out.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can prevent it by adding the following line to your &lt;code>~/.ssh/config&lt;/code> file head.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">Host *
ServerAliveInterval &lt;span class="m">30&lt;/span>
ServerAliveCountMax &lt;span class="m">2&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>I Hope this can resolve your problem.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>